{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0132uxpKwdpFaWTAHtTASQyM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Siu8xdnfijPAq9ULw8JHky","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLANEOF'\n# spark-pi Namespace — Maintenance Upgrade Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  \n**Namespace:** spark-pi  \n**Cluster context:** current configuration inspected; NO changes applied yet.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Snapshot\n\n### Deployments\n| Resource | Image | Replicas | CPU req/limit | Mem req/limit |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| spark-master | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 1 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-worker | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 1 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n\nWorker env: SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1\n\n### Service\n- spark-master ClusterIP 10.96.223.111, ports 7077 (spark) and 8080 (webui)\n- No worker service exists\n\n### Job: spark-pi\n- Image: apache/spark:3.5.3\n- Master: --master local[2]  ← runs in LOCAL mode, NOT on the cluster\n- Driver memory: --driver-memory 512m\n- Partitions: 1000\n- backoffLimit: 0 (no retries)\n- Resources: same as deployments (200m/500m CPU, 512Mi/1Gi mem)\n\n### RBAC\n- ServiceAccount: spark-pi\n- Role spark-pi-role: create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims\n- RoleBinding spark-pi-role-binding: binds spark-pi SA to that role\n\n### Missing\n- No PodDisruptionBudget (PDB)\n- No NetworkPolicy\n- No LimitRange / ResourceQuota\n- No liveness or readiness probes on either deployment\n- No worker Service resource\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Identified\n\n### CRITICAL\n\n**C1 — Job runs in local mode, not on the Spark cluster**  \nThe spark-pi Job uses `--master local[2]`, meaning it starts its own local Spark\ncontext inside the driver pod and completely ignores the running spark-master and\nspark-worker Deployments. The cluster resources are wasted on every job run.  \nFix: change `--master local[2]` to `--master spark://spark-master:7077` and\nadjust driver/executor resource flags accordingly.\n\n**C2 — SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY equals container memory limit (OOM risk)**  \nSPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G is set equal to the container memory limit of 1Gi. The JVM\nheap, off-heap buffers, and OS overhead together will exceed the cgroup limit,\ncausing OOM kills under any real workload.  \nFix: set SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=768m (75% of limit) and raise the memory limit to\n1.5Gi to give the JVM headroom, OR keep limit at 1Gi and reduce\nSPARK_WORKER_MEMORY to 768m.\n\n### HIGH\n\n**H1 — Single worker replica (no parallelism, SPOF)**  \nOne spark-worker pod means zero fault tolerance and minimal parallelism for jobs.  \nFix: scale spark-worker Deployment to replicas: 2 (minimum) or 3 for redundancy.\n\n**H2 — No liveness or readiness probes**  \nNeither spark-master nor spark-worker defines health probes. A silently hung or\ncrashed-but-not-exited process will receive traffic indefinitely.  \nFix: add readinessProbe (HTTP GET /json on port 8080 for master, 8081 for worker)\nand livenessProbe with appropriate initialDelaySeconds (60s) and periodSeconds (30s).\n\n**H3 — No PodDisruptionBudget**  \nDuring node maintenance or cluster upgrades, Kubernetes may evict both master and\nworker simultaneously. A PDB with minAvailable: 1 on spark-master prevents this.  \nFix: create PDB spark-master-pdb (minAvailable: 1, selector app: spark-master).\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n**M1 — Image version potentially outdated**  \nBoth deployments and the job use apache/spark:3.5.3. Evaluate the latest stable\nrelease in the apache/spark:3.5.x line for security patches before the change window.\nPin to a specific SHA digest after pulling to prevent unintended drift.\n\n**M2 — Job backoffLimit: 0 (no retry on transient failure)**  \nA single transient failure (node eviction, image-pull blip) permanently fails the\njob. A backoffLimit of 2 adds resilience with minimal risk.\n\n**M3 — No worker Service**  \nThe worker UI (port 8081) is not exposed via any Service. While not required for\ncomputation, it blocks observability of per-worker task state.  \nFix: create Service spark-worker (ClusterIP, port 8081) selecting app: spark-worker.\n\n### LOW / HARDENING\n\n**L1 — RBAC over-permissioned**  \nThe spark-pi-role grants delete on services and configmaps, and full CRUD on\npersistentvolumeclaims. No PVCs exist in the namespace; the application should not\nbe able to delete cluster network resources.  \nFix: remove delete verb from services; remove PVC resource entirely if unused;\nscope configmap verbs to create/get/update/patch (no delete).\n\n**L2 — No ResourceQuota or LimitRange**  \nNothing prevents a misconfigured job from consuming unbounded namespace resources.  \nFix: add a ResourceQuota (e.g., requests.cpu: 2, requests.memory: 4Gi,\nlimits.cpu: 4, limits.memory: 8Gi) and a LimitRange with default requests/limits\nmatching current deployment values.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Change Order and Verification Steps\n\nAll steps below are to be executed in a single maintenance window in the order\nlisted. Each step should be verified before proceeding to the next.\n\n### Step 0 — Pre-flight baseline (no changes)\n1. Record current pod states and resource versions:\n   kubectl get pods,deploy,job -n spark-pi -o wide\n2. Confirm spark-master is reachable from within the namespace:\n   kubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- curl -s http://spark-master:8080/json\n3. Record current job completion status to establish baseline.\n\nVerify: all 3 pods Running, master JSON endpoint responds.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — RBAC hardening (L1) — zero downtime\nApply updated Role removing delete from services, removing PVC resource, scoping\nconfigmap verbs:\n\n  rules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"services\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\",\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"update\",\"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\",\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"update\",\"patch\"]\n\nkubectl apply -f updated-role.yaml\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl auth can-i delete services --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n  # expected: no\n  kubectl auth can-i get configmaps --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n  # expected: yes\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Add ResourceQuota and LimitRange (L2) — zero downtime\nApply namespace-level quota and defaults before any deployment changes.\n\n  ResourceQuota spark-pi-quota:\n    requests.cpu: \"2\", requests.memory: 4Gi\n    limits.cpu: \"4\",   limits.memory: 8Gi\n\n  LimitRange spark-pi-limits:\n    default:        cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n    defaultRequest: cpu=200m, memory=512Mi\n\nkubectl apply -f quota.yaml -f limitrange.yaml\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl describe resourcequota -n spark-pi\n  kubectl describe limitrange -n spark-pi\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Fix SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY and add probes (C2, H2)\nPatch spark-worker Deployment:\n  - env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY: 1G → 768m\n  - resources.limits.memory: 1Gi → 1.5Gi  (or keep 1Gi and only lower the env)\n  - add readinessProbe: httpGet path=/json port=8081, initialDelaySeconds=30, periodSeconds=15\n  - add livenessProbe:  httpGet path=/json port=8081, initialDelaySeconds=60, periodSeconds=30\n\nPatch spark-master Deployment:\n  - add readinessProbe: httpGet path=/json port=8080, initialDelaySeconds=30, periodSeconds=15\n  - add livenessProbe:  httpGet path=/json port=8080, initialDelaySeconds=60, periodSeconds=30\n\nkubectl apply -f spark-master-updated.yaml\nkubectl apply -f spark-worker-updated.yaml\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master -n spark-pi\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get pods -n spark-pi   # all Running\n  kubectl describe deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi | grep -A5 Liveness\n  kubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- env | grep SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY\n  # expected: SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=768m\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Add PodDisruptionBudget for spark-master (H3)\n  apiVersion: policy/v1\n  kind: PodDisruptionBudget\n  metadata:\n    name: spark-master-pdb\n    namespace: spark-pi\n  spec:\n    minAvailable: 1\n    selector:\n      matchLabels:\n        app: spark-master\n\nkubectl apply -f spark-master-pdb.yaml\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get pdb -n spark-pi\n  # spark-master-pdb should show ALLOWED DISRUPTIONS: 0 (1 replica, 1 min available)\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Scale spark-worker to 2 replicas (H1)\nkubectl scale deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi --replicas=2\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker   # 2 pods Running\n  curl http://spark-master:8080/json | jq '.workers | length'\n  # expected: 2 (workers registered with master)\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Add worker Service (M3)\n  apiVersion: v1\n  kind: Service\n  metadata:\n    name: spark-worker\n    namespace: spark-pi\n  spec:\n    selector:\n      app: spark-worker\n    ports:\n    - name: webui\n      port: 8081\n      targetPort: 8081\n\nkubectl apply -f spark-worker-svc.yaml\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get svc spark-worker -n spark-pi\n\n---\n\n### Step 7 — Fix job to use cluster mode (C1) [REQUIRES JOB RECREATION]\nThe existing Job cannot be patched in-place. Plan:\na. Delete the completed/existing spark-pi Job:\n   kubectl delete job spark-pi -n spark-pi\nb. Apply updated Job manifest with:\n   --master spark://spark-master:7077\n   --deploy-mode client\n   --executor-memory 512m\n   --executor-cores 1\n   --num-executors 2\n   backoffLimit: 2\nc. Apply: kubectl apply -f spark-pi-job-updated.yaml\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi\n  kubectl logs -n spark-pi job/spark-pi -f\n  # Look for: \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" in the output\n  # Confirm workers on master UI show active tasks during execution:\n  kubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- \\\n    curl -s http://localhost:8080/json | jq '.workers[].activetasks'\n\n---\n\n### Step 8 — Image version upgrade (M1) [ROLLING RESTART]\nAfter verifying latest stable version (e.g., apache/spark:3.5.4 or newer 3.5.x):\n\na. Pull and verify the target image on all nodes (or via a pre-pull DaemonSet).\nb. Update all three manifests (spark-master, spark-worker Deployments, spark-pi Job template):\n   image: apache/spark:<new-version>\nc. Apply deployments and watch rollout:\n   kubectl apply -f spark-master-updated.yaml\n   kubectl apply -f spark-worker-updated.yaml\n   kubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master -n spark-pi\n   kubectl rollout status deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n\nVerify:\n  kubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}\\n{end}'\n  # All pods should show the new image tag\n  kubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- /opt/spark/bin/spark-submit --version\n  # Confirm version string matches upgrade target\n\n---\n\n### Step 9 — Post-upgrade smoke test\n1. Confirm all pods healthy:\n   kubectl get pods -n spark-pi   # all Running, no restarts\n2. Submit a fresh spark-pi job and verify completion:\n   kubectl delete job spark-pi -n spark-pi\n   kubectl apply -f spark-pi-job-updated.yaml\n   kubectl wait --for=condition=complete job/spark-pi -n spark-pi --timeout=300s\n   kubectl logs job/spark-pi -n spark-pi | grep \"Pi is roughly\"\n3. Confirm RBAC restriction still in place:\n   kubectl auth can-i delete services --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n   # expected: no\n4. Confirm ResourceQuota accounting:\n   kubectl describe resourcequota -n spark-pi\n5. Review master UI: curl http://spark-master:8080/json (expect 2 workers, 0 failed apps)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Plan\n\nEach step is independently reversible:\n- Steps 1-2 (RBAC/quota): kubectl delete/revert the applied manifest.\n- Steps 3-5 (deployment patches): kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master and deploy/spark-worker.\n- Step 6 (worker service): kubectl delete svc spark-worker -n spark-pi.\n- Step 7 (job): kubectl delete job spark-pi -n spark-pi; kubectl apply -f original-spark-pi-job.yaml.\n- Step 8 (image): kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master && kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-worker; re-run job with old image.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Change Summary Table\n\n| Step | Issue | Risk | Downtime? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | RBAC hardening | Low | No |\n| 2 | ResourceQuota/LimitRange | Low | No |\n| 3 | Worker memory fix + probes | Medium | Rolling restart (worker) |\n| 4 | PodDisruptionBudget | Low | No |\n| 5 | Scale worker to 2 replicas | Low | No |\n| 6 | Worker Service | Low | No |\n| 7 | Fix job cluster mode | Medium | Job recreation required |\n| 8 | Image version upgrade | Medium | Rolling restart (both deploys) |\n| 9 | Post-upgrade smoke test | — | — |\n\nTotal estimated window: 45–60 minutes including verification pauses.\nPLANEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in spark-pi namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2094,"cache_read_input_tokens":33471,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2094},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed3d7677-2db9-417d-9354-50444aae05da","uuid":"6b877629-5dbe-4cd9-99e0-b04a7c21a835","request_id":"req_011CcLBBian5cjUT3zR4N2uk"}
